html => structure of a webpage
css => design and layout of a webpage
javascript => behavior of a webpage

html
    - hypertext markup language
    - predefined-tags / element
    - head
    - body

xml - extensible markup language
<h1 align='center'>heading</h1>
<student rno='1' name='may' address='ygn'></student>

JSON
student{
    'rno':'1',
    'name':'may',
    'address':'ygn',
}
====================================================
html elements | attributes | properties
1. heading elements
    - h1(largest size) - h6 (smallest size) => h1,h2,h3,h4
        - align : left(default), right, center
2. Paragraph elements
    - p 
        - align : left(default), right, center,justify
3. Image elements
    - img
        - src : path of the image
        - alt : the description of the image which works when the image is not being loaded
    -favicon
4. List elements
    - ol
        - li => list item        
    - ul
        - li => list item
    - dl
        - li => list item
5. table element
6. anchor element

template
- index.html | default.html | home.html



Universal Design => everywhere, everyone


css - cascading stylesheet
    - for the design and layout of a webpage
    - place of css in the file
        - inline stylesheet
        - internal stylesheet
        - external stylesheet
    - structor of stylesheet rule
    selector {
        property:value;
        delcration2;
        delcration3;
        delcration4;
        .
        .
        .
        delcaration n;
    }
    - selector => html elements, ids, class, attributes
    - delcaration => property:value
    - property => html element's attributes
    - value => html attributes' values

    basic stylesheet rule
    background-color : color name, color hexa code, color rgb function;
    color :  color name, color hexa code, color rgb function;

    => font-style : normal, italic, oblique
    => font-weight : normal, bold, bolder, 100,200, ....900
    => text-decoration : none, overline, underline, line-through

    id => identification (unique)


box model => width, height, border, margin
margin : the distance between the two elements 
margin-top, right, bottom, left 
margin: 40px; // all sides
marign: 10px 20px; // t,b l,r 
margin: 10px 15px 20px; // t l,r b 
margin: 10px 15px 20px 25px;// t r b l => clockwise

padding : the distance between the content and the border of an element
padding-top, right, bottom, left 
padding: 40px; // all sides
padding: 10px 20px; // t,b l,r 
padding: 10px 15px 20px; // t l,r b 
padding: 10px 15px 20px 25px;// t r b l => clockwise